ke `extractFromRequest` and `auth.bearer[String]` for added security. It's vital to ensure that our public API remains up-to-date and properly tested, especially for secured endpoints requiring bearer authentication. Existing tests don't cover these security details yet.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering test requirements**\\\\n\\\\nI’m thinking about how to add a test. I need to check if I require imports, specifically `auth` under `sttp.tapir.*`, but no extras. It seems the class should be public and top-level — Class in Scala is public by default. \\\\n\\\\nI’m also recalling that the method should take less than 60 seconds. I’ll use `withServer`, perhaps create a constant for the expected token, and add the new test after the error without altering any existing logic. Exact edits are crucial!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_CBTxLt3BiApMtJjYR48Z6pUb|fc_0b2476af74ae26ad016a2a85549ee88190a619cb3bc474d3c3\", \"name\": \"edit\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/com.softwaremill.sttp.tapir/tapir-pekko-http-server_3/1.13.18/src/test/scala/com_softwaremill_sttp_tapir/tapir_pekko_http_server_3/Tapir_pekko_http_server_3Test.scala\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"  @Test\\n  def shouldDispatchAmongSeveralServerEndpoints(): Unit = {\\n\", \"newText\": \"  @Test\\n  def shouldAuthenticateBearerTokenUsingTapirSecurityLogic(): Unit = {\\n    withServer { executionContext =>\\n      implicit val ec: ExecutionContext = executionContext\\n      val securedEndpoint = endpoint.get\\n        .securityIn(auth.bearer[String]())\\n        .in(\\\"secure\\\")\\n        .out(stringBody)\\n        .errorOut(statusCode.and(stringBody))\\n\\n      PekkoHttpServerInterpreter().toRoute(\\n        securedEndpoint\\n          .serverSecurityLogic { token =>\\n            Future.successful {\\n              if (token == \\\"access-token\\\") {\\n                Right(token)\\n              } else {\\n                Left((StatusCode.Unau